{"word":"παρωθέω","slug":"παρωθέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>παρωθέω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>-ώσω</el>) <b>-ωθήσω</b></el> <p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to push aside, reject, slight</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be set aside, slighted</i>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to push away from oneself, reject, renounce</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschines'>Aeschin.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b>of Time, <i>to put off</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}